# GitHub Actions (this repo)

When editing workflows under `.github/workflows/`:

## Node / runner runtime

- Prefer **Node 24** for `actions/setup-node` (`node-version: 24`).
- Do **not** pin actions that still declare the Node 20 action runtime — GitHub forces Node 24 and emits deprecation noise.
- Docs mentioned via `@GitHub Actions` are reference only; always verify current majors against each action’s latest release before changing pins.

## Preferred pins (update when bumps land)

| Action | Prefer |
|--------|--------|
| `actions/checkout` | `@v7` |
| `actions/setup-node` | `@v7` |
| `actions/upload-pages-artifact` | `@v5` |
| `actions/deploy-pages` | `@v5` |

If a step fails after a major bump, check that action’s README for breaking changes; do not silently downgrade to Node 20 eras (`checkout@v4`, `setup-node@v4`, `deploy-pages@v4`).

## This project’s Pages deploy

- Trigger on `main` (+ `workflow_dispatch`).
- Build with `npm ci` + `npm run build`; artifact path `dist`.
- Vite `base` is `/crypto-repo-tracker/` in production builds — do not change the Pages source away from GitHub Actions without updating `vite.config.ts`.

## CI (`ci.yml`)

- Trigger on **every push** (any branch) + `workflow_dispatch`.
- Blocking: `typecheck`, `lint`, `format`, `check`.
- Non-blocking: `npm audit --omit=dev` with `continue-on-error: true`.
- Same Node 24 / action majors as above.

## Rule vs skill

- Keep workflow conventions in this **project rule** (file-scoped).
- A **skill** is only needed for a reusable multi-repo procedure; don’t duplicate this as a skill unless asked to share it across projects.
